'''''Shots''''' '''On-line''' is a mobile [[web application]] that is a resource on [[immunization]]s for [[smartphone]]s and other handheld devices. It was developed by the Group on Immunization Education of the Society of Teachers of Family Medicine (STFM). It is available for [[iPhone]]/[[iPod Touch]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], and [[BlackBerry]] devices. '''Shots''' software is also available for standard [[Palm (PDA)|palm]] and [[Windows]] based [[PDA]]s. Information is easily accessed via [[drop-down menu]]s.<ref>[http://www.immunizationed.org/ShotsOnline.aspx STFM: Child Immunization schedule]</ref>
'''Shots''' contains the unified, [[Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices|ACIP]]-approved childhood, adolescent, adult, catch-up and medical indications schedules for the United States. Drop-down menus provide details about every vaccine and include: Basics, High Risk Indications, Adverse Reactions, [[Contraindications]], Catch-Up, Administration, Risk Communications, Brand Names, [[Epidemiology]] and Pictures of Vaccine Preventable Diseases. As new vaccines become available and recommendations are made, they are added to the applications.
