'''Tim Seldin''' (born June 16, 1946) is an author, educator and the President of The Montessori Foundation and Chair of The International Montessori Council.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.montessori.org/the-montessori-foundation-2 |title=The Montessori Foundation &#124; Montessori Foundation &#124; MFA &#124; IMC |publisher=Montessori.org |date= |accessdate=2018-06-26}}</ref> His more than forty years of experience in [[Montessori education]] includes twenty-two years as Headmaster of the [[Barrie School]] in Silver Spring, Maryland, of which he also attended. He has also served as the Director of the [[Institute for Advanced Montessori Studies]] and as Head of the New Gate School in Sarasota, Florida.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://westendmontessori.com/wems-school/excerpt_montessori_way.pdf |title=Excerpt |website=westendmontessori.com |format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yourobserver.com/article/new-montessori-school-won't-forget-building's-history|title=NewGate opens in new campus in Lakewood Ranch - East County - Your Observer|date=7 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref> He write the book ''How To Raise An Amazing Child the Montessori Way'', and conducts weekly [[webinar]]s about Montessori Education.<ref>{{cite web|author=Abigail Van Buren |url=https://www.montessori.org/webcasts-for-montessori-educators |title=Webcasts for Montessori Educators &#124; Montessori Foundation &#124; MFA &#124; IMC |publisher=Montessori.org |date=2017-02-15 |accessdate=2018-06-26}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Seldin is married to Joyce St. Giermaine. They have three children: Marc, Michelle, and Caitlin, and he is stepfather to Chelsea and Robin. He lives on a small ranch in Sarasota, Florida.{{cn|date=July 2018}}

